quran[33]{c,v,t}:
  55,46,For those who fear the Station of their Lord there are two Gardens
  55,47,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,48,Shaded by spreading branches
  55,49,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,50,In them are two clear flowing springs
  55,51,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,52,In them are two kinds of every fruit
  55,53,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,54,"They will be reclining on couches lined with rich brocade, the fruits of the Gardens hanging close to hand"
  55,55,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,56,"In them are maidens with eyes for them alone, untouched before them by either man or jinn"
  55,57,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,58,Like precious gems of ruby and pearl
  55,59,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,60,Will the reward for doing good be anything other than good
  55,61,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,62,As well as those two there will be two other Gardens
  55,63,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,64,Of deep viridian green
  55,65,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,66,In them are two gushing springs
  55,67,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,68,In them are fruits and date-palms and pomegranates
  55,69,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,70,"In them are sweet, lovely maidens"
  55,71,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,72,"Dark-eyed, secluded in cool pavilions"
  55,73,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,74,Untouched before them by either man or jinn
  55,75,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,76,Reclining on green quilts and exquisite rugs
  55,77,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,78,"Blessed be the name of your Lord, Master of Majesty and Generosity"